
[1]weighty

   WEIGHTY, a.

   1. Having great weight; heavy; ponderous; as a weighty body.

   2. Important; forcible; momentous; adapted to turn the balance in the
   mind, or to convince; as weighty reasons; weighty matters; weighty
   considerations or arguments.

   3. Rigorous; severe; as our weightier judgment. [Not in use.]
